    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Irrespective of whether signing is done by the validator or elsewhere, we should implement a degree of protection against getting slashed at the validator end of things.\r\n\r\nIn principle it is fairly easy:\r\n  - Persist the number of the slot I last proposed a block in, and the block root\r\n  - Persist the last source and last target I attested to along with the attestation root\r\n\r\nUsing these data it is simple to avoid sending for signing anything that might get me slashed. We store the previous roots, because we _are_ allowed to re-sign/re-broadcast the same block/attestation if we wish.\r\n\r\nWe should also make these values (maybe excluding the hashes) exportable/importable so that we can safely move keys between validator processes potentially on different hardware.",
