    "body": "@benjaminion We now record the last values in a yaml file so they're human readable and can be copied or even manually created for a different client.  I could see some benefit in creating Cli options to specify  values and have it create the file automatically (though the syntax would be awkward) or have a subcommand to import slashing protection which copies over files and picks the higher value if there are some overlapping validators.\n\nI'm not sure either of those are actually worth it at the moment though.  How far do you think we should go at the moment to support moving these validator records around?",
